The Federal Government has set up a committee of broadcast and industry stakeholders to look into and advise the government on the best way to mitigate the effect of the corona virus pandemic on the industry.  The Honorable Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, who made this known during a meeting with the Broadcasting Organizations of Nigeria (BON) in Abuja, said his Ministry has approved the request by the National Broadcasting Commission (NBC) to grant a two-month licence fee waiver for terrestrial broadcast stations in Nigeria. The Minister reiterated its resolve to address the challenges bedeviling the Broadcast and Creative Industry which is a very critical sector of the nation's economy and a major plank of the economic diversification policy of this Administration.  Earlier, the Vice Chairman of the Broadcasting Organization of Nigeria (BON) Mr. Godfrey Ohuabunwa said the broadcast industry especially the Journalist in the front-line are at the risk of being infected and urged the federal government to provide protective equipment, life insurance packages and also make available loans for broadcast stations. He however hoped that the committee set up by the government would approach the challenges faced by the industry with all sense of urgency in order to prevent media houses from laying off their employees due to the Covid-19 pandemic.